! $1,500 for contributions to a family health plan.
If the credit exceeds the income taxes due on the resident individual's
income, the amount of the credit not used to offset income taxes is not
carried forward as tax credits against the resident individual's subsequent
years' income tax liability and is not refunded to the individual. The
executive director of the department of revenue is required to adopt rules
implementing the credit.
